				<div class=3D"elementor-widget-container">
					<h3 class=3D"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default">8. Plan f=
or a =E2=80=98coming home=E2=80=99, post-travels budget</h3>				</div>
				</div>
				<div class=3D"elementor-element elementor-element-6353867 elementor-wid=
get elementor-widget-text-editor" data-id=3D"6353867" data-element_type=3D"=
widget" data-widget_type=3D"text-editor.default">
				<div class=3D"elementor-widget-container">
									<p id=3D"viewer-fvu8k">I know, you=E2=80=99ve not even started you=
r travels and I=E2=80=99m talking about coming home! This seems super borin=
g, but the last thing you want after your travels are over is to get home t=
o absolutely nothing. Plan to put a little aside so that you have some mone=
y when you come home to help set yourself up again. For example, you might =
need to put some money aside to buy a new car, or for the first couple of m=
onth=E2=80=99s deposit in a rental unit.</p>
<p><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>
<p id=3D"viewer-bebna"><em>Task: Write down things you would need to pay fo=
r upon your return and add an estimated cost for this to your Travel Budget=
 Spreadsheet. (I would also make sure that you keep this money in a separat=
e bank account to your travel pot, so that you aren=E2=80=99t tempted to di=
p into it)!</em></p>								</div>
				</div>
					</div>
		</div>
					</div>
		</section>
				<section class=3D"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-ele=
ment elementor-element-7057850 elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-he=
ight-default elementor-section-height-default" data-id=3D"7057850" data-ele=
ment_type=3D"section">
						<div class=3D"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default">
					<div class=3D"elementor-column elementor-col-100 elementor-top-column =
elementor-element elementor-element-bc854f7" data-id=3D"bc854f7" data-eleme=
nt_type=3D"column">
			<div class=3D"elementor-widget-wrap elementor-element-populated">
						<div class=3D"elementor-element elementor-element-4de3f15 elementor-w=
idget elementor-widget-heading" data-id=3D"4de3f15" data-element_type=3D"wi=
dget" data-widget_type=3D"heading.default">
				<div class=3D"elementor-widget-container">
					<h3 class=3D"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default">9. Decide=
 on a date to start travelling</h3>				</div>
				</div>
				<div class=3D"elementor-element elementor-element-9038096 elementor-wid=
get elementor-widget-text-editor" data-id=3D"9038096" data-element_type=3D"=
widget" data-widget_type=3D"text-editor.default">
				<div class=3D"elementor-widget-container">
									<p id=3D"viewer-1690m">Now you know how much money you need to sav=
e for your trip, plan how long that will take you to save. Set up a direct =
debit into your savings account, or open up a specific =E2=80=98travel acco=
unt=E2=80=99 and transfer money into there each week, fortnight or month.</=
p>
<p><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>
<p id=3D"viewer-feh0r">Having a goal of how much you need to save and a dat=
e to work towards will make it easier for you to focus on saving for your t=
ravels. Be realistic with your timeline. If you want to set off sooner, mak=
e a plan for how this could be possible for you.</p>
<p><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>
<p id=3D"viewer-1tpdh">My husband and I chose not to work. We made a consci=
ous decision to take some time out, away from our busy careers and simply e=
njoy travelling. We planned for this from the beginning and we were really =
strict with ourselves, sticking to our plan to save.</p>
<p><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>
<p id=3D"viewer-1lm4i">Of course, this may not suit everyone and if you don=
=E2=80=99t want to wait until you have saved enough, or perhaps you want to=
 be able to travel with no end date, then that=E2=80=99s great! But make su=
re that you plan for that too. Could you save 50% of what you need initiall=
y, then work remotely to earn more as you go? There are lots of ways to ear=
n money online whilst you=E2=80=99re travelling. Or, depending on the count=
ry you are in, you could also get a working visa to help top up your travel=
 pot.</p>
<p><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>
<p id=3D"viewer-173cq">You could also consider joining a Workaway program w=
here you work for a few hours a day in return for free accommodation. Or ho=
w about being a house sitter or dog sitter, if you don=E2=80=99t mind stayi=
ng in one place for a few weeks? These are all great ways to get free accom=
modation which is a great help to your budget.</p>								</div>
				</div>
					</div>
		</div>
					</div>
		</section>
