				<div class=3D"elementor-widget-container">
					<span id=3D"elementor-toc__heading-anchor-4" class=3D"elementor-menu-a=
nchor "></span><h2 class=3D"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default"=
>How to keep your travel budget on track (and not overspend!)</h2>				</div=
>
				</div>
				<div class=3D"elementor-element elementor-element-c265b92 elementor-wid=
get elementor-widget-text-editor" data-id=3D"c265b92" data-element_type=3D"=
widget" data-widget_type=3D"text-editor.default">
				<div class=3D"elementor-widget-container">
									<p id=3D"viewer-deu3n">You=E2=80=99ve spent many months saving har=
d and finally the time has come for you to set off on your travels! (YAY!) =
Whilst it=E2=80=99s easy to get swept up in the excitement of travelling (o=
f course you should be excited, travel is the best!), it is important that =
you keep a track of your spending. It sounds boring, but trust me, you don=
=E2=80=99t want to find out that you=E2=80=99ve spent all your hard earned =
money too quickly and now have to cut your trip short.</p>
<p><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>
<p id=3D"viewer-80jed">So, to make sure that doesn=E2=80=99t happen, here=
=E2=80=99s my 3 top tips for keeping track of your travel budget whilst tra=
velling:</p>								</div>
				</div>
					</div>
		</div>
					</div>
		</section>
				<section class=3D"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-ele=
ment elementor-element-eacd9d4 elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-he=
ight-default elementor-section-height-default" data-id=3D"eacd9d4" data-ele=
ment_type=3D"section">
						<div class=3D"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default">
					<div class=3D"elementor-column elementor-col-100 elementor-top-column =
elementor-element elementor-element-47f7329" data-id=3D"47f7329" data-eleme=
nt_type=3D"column">
			<div class=3D"elementor-widget-wrap elementor-element-populated">
						<div class=3D"elementor-element elementor-element-a57bc4f elementor-w=
idget elementor-widget-heading" data-id=3D"a57bc4f" data-element_type=3D"wi=
dget" data-widget_type=3D"heading.default">
				<div class=3D"elementor-widget-container">
					<h3 class=3D"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default">1. Track =
your daily travel spend</h3>				</div>
				</div>
				<div class=3D"elementor-element elementor-element-2ede727 elementor-wid=
get elementor-widget-text-editor" data-id=3D"2ede727" data-element_type=3D"=
widget" data-widget_type=3D"text-editor.default">
				<div class=3D"elementor-widget-container">
									<p id=3D"viewer-d3umo">Don=E2=80=99t worry, I won=E2=80=99t be sug=
gesting that you fill in a spreadsheet everyday (although you can if you wa=
nt to!). I use the <strong><a href=3D"https://travel-spend.com/" target=3D"=
_blank" rel=3D"noreferrer noopener">Travel Spend </a></strong>app religious=
ly, in fact I=E2=80=99m a little bit obsessed with it! It is without a doub=
t my favourite travel app. There=E2=80=99s a paid version where you can hav=
e multiple trips displaying at once, and add your own custom categories, bu=
t to be honest, I=E2=80=99ve been fine with just using the free version for=
 the past year.</p>
<p><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>
<p id=3D"viewer-4mc1l">I prefer to have a new entry on the travel spend app=
 by country, as I have different daily budgets for each country. To get sta=
rted, simply add the name of the country you are starting in, add the total=
 budget you have set yourself for that country, as well as the beginning an=
d end dates you are there. The app will then automatically calculate what y=
our daily spend should be based on your total budget and number of days =E2=
=80=93 this should match the daily budget figure you have on your Travel Bu=
dget Spreadsheet.</p>
<p><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>
<p id=3D"viewer-e2i8q">Each time I buy something, I enter it onto the app, =
even if it=E2=80=99s just a single bottle of water. The app will total how =
much you have spent that day, as well as showing you how much of your total=
 budget you have remaining.</p>
<p><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>
<p id=3D"viewer-65mdn">Try not to get too caught up on what you have spent =
each day, as some days you will go over budget and some days you will go un=
der. You need to focus on the =E2=80=98daily average spend=E2=80=99, and as=
 long as this matches (or is close to) the figure you have budgeted for, yo=
u are on track.</p>								</div>
				</div>
					</div>
		</div>
					</div>
		</section>
				<section class=3D"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-ele=
ment elementor-element-c8c4351 elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-he=
ight-default elementor-section-height-default" data-id=3D"c8c4351" data-ele=
ment_type=3D"section">
						<div class=3D"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default">
					<div class=3D"elementor-column elementor-col-100 elementor-top-column =
elementor-element elementor-element-6dbd3c1" data-id=3D"6dbd3c1" data-eleme=
nt_type=3D"column">
			<div class=3D"elementor-widget-wrap elementor-element-populated">
						<div class=3D"elementor-element elementor-element-dc51d55 elementor-w=
idget elementor-widget-heading" data-id=3D"dc51d55" data-element_type=3D"wi=
dget" data-widget_type=3D"heading.default">
				<div class=3D"elementor-widget-container">
					<h3 class=3D"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default">2. Record=
 your total spend per location</h3>				</div>
				</div>
				<div class=3D"elementor-element elementor-element-ca8e89a elementor-wid=
get elementor-widget-text-editor" data-id=3D"ca8e89a" data-element_type=3D"=
widget" data-widget_type=3D"text-editor.default">
				<div class=3D"elementor-widget-container">
									<p id=3D"viewer-18nsm">Once your time is up in a country or destin=
ation, record your total spend in your Travel Budget Spreadsheet. This is a=
 good way to keep track of your actual spend and you can also compare it ag=
ainst the budget you had forecast for that destination to see if you were s=
ignificantly over or under budget.</p>
<p><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>
<p id=3D"viewer-3e6l9">Noticing any discrepancies in this way will allow yo=
u to make any adjustments you might need to the rest of your budget. For ex=
ample, if you are under budget, you know that you can afford to have a coup=
le of treats in your next destination. But if you have gone way over budget=
, you need to look at where you can claw back some money, or decide to earn=
 some extra money as you travel.</p>
<p><!-- /wp:paragraph --><!-- wp:paragraph --></p>
<p id=3D"viewer-rslm">If you are travelling to several destinations, and ar=
e using the free version of the Travel Spend app, you will need to delete y=
our current country in the app in order to record your spend in a new count=
ry. So, just make sure that you have inputted your total spend into your Tr=
avel Budget Spreadsheet before deleting that country in the app!</p>							=
	</div>
				</div>
					</div>
		</div>
					</div>
		</section>
