				<div class=3D"elementor-widget-container">
					<h3 class=3D"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default">3. Make a=
ny adjustments needed to your ongoing expenses budget</h3>				</div>
				</div>
				<div class=3D"elementor-element elementor-element-db64da6 elementor-wid=
get elementor-widget-text-editor" data-id=3D"db64da6" data-element_type=3D"=
widget" data-widget_type=3D"text-editor.default">
				<div class=3D"elementor-widget-container">
									<p>If any of the regular payments you are making as =E2=80=98ongoi=
ng expenses=E2=80=99 change, you will need to adjust this in your spreadshe=
et and make sure that you have enough in your =E2=80=98ongoing expenses=E2=
=80=99 pot to cover any additional costs or price rises on things like stor=
age unit hire, insurance or subscriptions.</p>								</div>
				</div>
					</div>
		</div>
					</div>
		</section>
				<section class=3D"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-ele=
ment elementor-element-2d6674d elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-he=
ight-default elementor-section-height-default" data-id=3D"2d6674d" data-ele=
ment_type=3D"section">
						<div class=3D"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default">
					<div class=3D"elementor-column elementor-col-100 elementor-top-column =
elementor-element elementor-element-217ab26" data-id=3D"217ab26" data-eleme=
nt_type=3D"column">
			<div class=3D"elementor-widget-wrap elementor-element-populated">
						<div class=3D"elementor-element elementor-element-e3e4ca3 elementor-w=
idget elementor-widget-image" data-id=3D"e3e4ca3" data-element_type=3D"widg=
